Wilderness empires are blocked from taking the [b]Become the Crisis[/b] and [b]Cosmogenesis[/b] ascension perks in vanilla. This mod removes that restriction.

[h2]What it does[/h2]

Adds Wilderness-only versions of two crisis ascension perks:
[list]
    [*][b]Become the Crisis[/b] (Nemesis DLC)
    [*][b]Cosmogenesis[/b] (Machine Age DLC)
[/list]

When you select either perk, the mod grants you the real vanilla version behind the scenes. This means:
[list]
    [*]All crisis progression, menace objectives, and crisis levels work normally
    [*]All technologies, buildings, and events tied to the crisis path work normally
    [*]Only one ascension perk slot is consumed
    [*]Other empires interact with you as a crisis empire as usual
[/list]

[b]Galactic Hyperthermia[/b] (Cosmic Storms DLC) is not included. Its terraforming focus conflicts heavily with Wilderness, which also ties deeply into terraforming mechanics.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/fVVaDCS.gif[/img]

[h2]Feedback[/h2]

Feedback is quite welcome in the comments, but look at Known Issues below, first.

[h2]Known Issues[/h2]
Since these are minor and/or nontrivial to fix, I have no immediate plans to fix them. Let me know in comments if it particularly irks you.

[list]
    [*]When you choose the perk, the perk will actually appear in the [b]next[/b] perk slot, leaving a gap. This gap will close in a day.
    [*]When you hover over the perk, it will show no effects. A day after you select the perk, the effects will be correct.
[/list]

[h2]Requirements[/h2]

[list]
    [*]BioGenesis DLC (for the Wilderness origin)
    [*]Nemesis DLC (for Become the Crisis) and/or Machine Age DLC (for Cosmogenesis)
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]

This mod does not override any vanilla files. It should not conflict with any other mod.
